                       "message":  "ARCH-LINT-EDITOR-BOUNDARIES: revive dead editor-state-ownership Part B + add editor-shell loader-free rule\n\nAudit P1. Two architecture-lint fixes (lint/policy only — no product behavior\nchange).\n\n1. editor-state-ownership Part B was DEAD CODE: FORBIDDEN_IMPORT_PREFIXES held\n   bare names (\"cad_core\") but real imports are rge_-prefixed (use rge_cad_core::),\n   and the leading-segment match was exact, so it never fired (same prefix-\n   mismatch class as the Audit-5/6 fixes). The lint reported PASS while\n   editor-state really imports rge_cad_core types. Fix:\n   - normalize_crate_root() strips an optional leading rge_ before comparison.\n   - cad-core ID/tag ALLOWLIST {BRepOwnerId, BRepFaceId, CuboidFaceTag} (verified\n     pure identifier/tag value types) is permitted; leaf-inspection flags any\n     other cad-core import (an authority type, or a glob that can\u0027t be verified).\n     Every other forbidden crate stays a whole-crate ban.\n\n2. forbidden-dep rule 7 (new): rge-editor-shell must stay loader-free — cannot\n   depend on rge-scene-loader or rge-data. Closes the convention-only\n   \"editor-shell is loader-free\" drift vector from the #274-#279 save arc (the\n   binary owns the loader edge via the SceneOpenHook/save-hook seam).\n\nTests: editor_state_ownership_test gains 5 cases (rge_cad_core authority import\nfails; the {BRepFaceId,BRepOwnerId} + CuboidFaceTag allowlists pass; a mixed\nimport flags only the authority type; a glob fails). forbidden_dep gains rule-7\npure-logic + synthetic-workspace fixtures; the real-workspace canary renamed to\ncurrent_workspace_passes_all_rules.\n\nReal-workspace lint run: all 10 lints PASS (0 violations) — editor-state-ownership\nnow genuinely passes (allowlist covers face_selection.rs), rule 7 holds.\n\n3 files (lint tool + tests), 0 Cargo.toml, no new lint (still 10), no main.rs\nchange. Gate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10 arch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
