                       "message":  "ARCH-LINT-EDITOR-BOUNDARIES: fix root-braced use-group bypass in editor-state-ownership Part B\n\nCorrection round (post-exec review NEEDS_CORRECTION, Codex).\n\nBlocking finding: root-braced `use {rge_cad_core::BRepNode};` parses as a root\nUseTree::Group, which has no single leading segment. leading_segment() returned\nNone for it and visit_item_use() did not recurse, so the authority import passed\nwith 0 violations — a real bypass of the policy Part B hardens (not cad-core-\nspecific). The leading_segment() doc also wrongly claimed root groups were\n\"handled by recursion\".\n\nFix: extract the per-tree logic into a recursive\nForbiddenImportVisitor::check_use_tree(). A root-braced UseTree::Group is\ndecomposed — each child is checked as its own independent import tree. Non-group\ntrees run the existing logic unchanged (normalize leading segment, cad-core\nleaf-inspection against the ID/tag allowlist with glob/rename handling on THIS\nsubtree, whole-crate ban for every other forbidden crate). visit_item_use is now\njust self.check_use_tree(\u0026node.tree). leading_segment() doc corrected.\n\nTests: editor_state_ownership_test +4 root-braced cases (now 16) — cad-core\nauthority (BRepNode) fails; non-cad forbidden (components_render) fails;\nallowlisted {BRepFaceId, kernel EntityId} passes; cad-core glob fails.\n\n2 files (forbidden_dep.rs rule 7 unchanged), +201/-26, 0 Cargo.toml, nightly fmt\nclean, still 10 lints, no product source touched. Gate: VERIFY OK (7/7), 10/10\narch lints.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
